title: Facebook's Free Cash Flow Grew in Q4, Significantly Raising Its Value
text: Facebook grew its free cash flow in Q4, significantly raising its value. Facebook stock is worth 40% more or $374.53, based on its powerful FCF margins.

title: Facebook faces new UK class action after data harvesting scandal
text: Facebook is facing a second London High Court class action over allegations it failed to protect the personal details of about one million people in England and Wales, in the latest lawsuit to spring from a scandal over data harvesting.

title: Australia does not want to see Google or Facebook leave, but they must follow the rules
text: Prime Minister Scott Morrison has made it clear to Google that the Australian parliament is on track to pass into law a media bill that would make digital platforms pay publishers for news, says Communications Minister Paul Fletcher.

title: Australia's media bill could become law 'fairly soon' despite Google and Facebook objections, minister says
text: The so-called news media bargaining code would require digital platforms like Google, Facebook to pay local media outlets and publishers to link their content.
